                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Andhra invitation to Tatas
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Hyderabad, Aug. 25: Andhra Pradesh today joined the list of states that have invited Tata Motors to build the Nano on their soil if the company left Singur.        
	M. Pratap, an official in the chief ministers office, said Andhra was ready to offer land and all other facilities to Tata Motors. The state will send a formal letter to the company tomorrow.        
	In Visakhapatnam, the land offered to Volkswagen, which chose Maharashtra, is still vacant.         
	In todays letter to Mamata Banerjee, Bengal chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee had referred to the appeals from other states to the Tatas. In view of that, you, too, must be wanting the project in this state as a responsible Opposition leader, the chief minister said.                                                                                                                                                                         
